            <div class='post' itemprop='articleBody'>
              <p>Hello,</p>
<p>It will be very helpful to be able to allow users that are not admin to change the permissions of other  usersâ€™ queries from the same group.</p>
<p>The problem is that users from one group build dashboards/queries and the rest of the group canâ€™t edit/change it if needed.</p>
<p>General solution:<br>
Maybe it can be implemented like additional built-in group (e.x. <code>sub_group_admin</code>).<br>
In case if current user is added to this group (manually of course) so current user can edit all dashboards/queries of other users from all groups (except built-in ones) to which current user belongs to.</p>
<p>Solution by groups:<br>
It can be implemented per group, but in this case current user should have another property (like <code>permissions.group_admin = true</code> or <code>group_admin = true</code>).</p>
            </div>

